What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you can get Prof. Hadley, I highly recommend it! She's amazing! You'll love going to class and you'll get a lot out of it!

A great intro-level language class. It is designed where you go through units very quickly (one every 1.5 weeks or so) but I found it very manageable and not difficult in concept. A low-maintenance class with a a noticeable outcome.

I would definitely recommend taking Italian! It is a beautiful language that is being taught by one of the most dedicated and caring department at Yale. You are not just taking a language course; you becoming part of a close knit community.
I would indeed recommend the course to another student. However, I would make him/her fully aware of how fast paced it is as well as the amount of homework and exams.
